---
**Overall Performance:**
- **Average Open-loop Baseline Error**: `0.0229 m`
- **Average Fully-Blind RL Recovered Error**: `0.0102 m`
- **Average Improvement**: **`50.80%`**

### Conclusion
Even after completely shutting off the internal PCC mathematical "hints", the RL network was still able to **recover an average of 50.8% of the drifted error** caused by the external forces. It is relying explicitly on the visual tracking error feedback. This is conclusive evidence that the RL model independently learned a robust kinematic corrective policy, without relying on background physical models to do the math for it!
